		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;The idea...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;New page&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;==My Goal==&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
I want to get the tutorial lists posted on D3W here...&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
[http://www.doom3world.org/phpbb2/viewtopic.php?f=1&amp;amp;t=3017]&lt;br /&gt;
[http://www.doom3world.org/phpbb2/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;amp;t=11893]&lt;br /&gt;
[http://www.doom3world.org/phpbb2/viewtopic.php?f=3&amp;amp;t=11896]&lt;br /&gt;
[http://www.doom3world.org/phpbb2/viewtopic.php?f=4&amp;amp;t=2625]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
... ported over to the wiki.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The intention is to get these lists consolidated, organized, and posted somewhere where they can be maintained by the community.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
I'd also like to screen through the list and remove tutorials that cover subjects that are already covered in depth here. Case in point the keyboard shortcuts tutorial isn't necessary. We have such a page dedicated to the topic on the wiki already.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
At any rate, I've ported the first post from the first link over. I'll work on it some more later if someone doesn't beat me to it.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
--[[User:Rich|Rich]] 08:18, 4 September 2007 (CEST)&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Rich</name></author>	</entry>

